You need two pieces: a **navigation guard** in `AppShell` and **`BackButtonBehavior`** on the page.

### 1. Custom "Cancel" back button on EditProductPage

```xml
<!-- EditProductPage.xaml -->
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.EditProductPage">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding CancelCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- your form content -->
</ContentPage>
```

### 2. ViewModel with cancel logic and dirty-tracking

```csharp
public partial class EditProductViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task CancelAsync()
    {
        if (HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
                "Unsaved Changes",
                "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
                "Discard", "Stay");

            if (!discard)
                return; // stay on page
        }

        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

### 3. Guard the hardware/swipe back in AppShell

The custom `Command` above handles the **button tap**, but the user can also swipe back or press the Android hardware back button. Guard that with `OnNavigating`:

```csharp
// AppShell.xaml.cs
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    // Only intercept "pop" navigation (back gesture / hardware back)
    if (args.Source != ShellNavigationSource.Pop)
        return;

    if (Shell.Current.CurrentPage?.BindingContext
            is EditProductViewModel { HasUnsavedChanges: true })
    {
        // Must get deferral BEFORE any await
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await Shell.Current.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- Call `args.GetDeferral()` **before** any `await` — otherwise Shell completes the navigation before your dialog resolves.
- Call `deferral.Complete()` in **all** code paths (discard or stay).
- The `BackButtonBehavior.Command` bypasses `OnNavigating`, so the dialog logic lives in the VM for button taps and in `OnNavigating` for swipe/hardware back.
- Check `args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop` so you don't block tab switches or forward navigation.
